==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Equipollent
<hw>E`qui*pol"lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aequipollens</ets>; <ets>aequus</ets> equal + <ets>pollens</ets>,
<ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>pollere</ets> to be strong, able: cf.
F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧quipollent</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having equal
power or force; equivalent.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>Having equivalent signification
and reach; expressing the same thing, but differently.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equipollently</ent>⟦br⟧
